fq = 500
In [235]:
def getwindowBorders(secondNumber, windowSize, samplingRate):
    window_start = 0
    window_end = 500
    window_start= (secondNumber-1)*window_end
    window_end= window_start+int(window_end*windowSize)
    return window_start, window_end
In [236]:
fig = plt.figure(figsize=(15,4))
figure_details = fig.add_subplot()
figure_details.set_ylabel('mV')
figure_details.set_xlabel('seconds')
figure_details.set_title('ECG Signal')

figure_details.plot(data.Time[start:end],data.C4[start:end], c='r')
plt.show()
In [238]:
list_EEG = list_columns[1:-1]
for i in list_EEG[:-1]:
    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(15,1))
    figure_details = fig.add_subplot()  
    if i == 'Fp1':
        plt.title("EEG Signals")
    figure_details.set_ylabel(i)
    figure_details.plot(data['Time'],data[i], c=np.random.rand(3,))
    figure_details.axes.get_xaxis().set_ticks([])
    figure_details.axes.get_yaxis().set_ticks([])
    plt.show()

from scipy.fftpack import  rfft, rfftfreq 
fig, axs = plt.subplots()
fig.set_figheight(3)
fig.set_figwidth(15)
yTf = rfft(data[data.columns[10]].values)
xTf = rfftfreq(N, 1 / fq)
plt.plot(xTf, np.abs(yTf))
plt.show()
